juniBgpMIB.name: juniBgpMIB

revisions.description: Added support for BGP conditional advertisement
Added support for BGP over TCPv6.
Changed DEFVAL for for juniBgpDefaultIPv4Unicast, juniBgpAutomaticRouteTargetFilter, juniBgpGlobalRibOutEnabled juniBgpEnabled and changed range for juniBgpGlobalConfigKeepAliveInterval.

Obsoleted Storage group. Added the next-hop-unchanged attribute to the peer address-family and peer-group address-family. Obsoleted the address-family IP and IP-service profile attributes. Removed the Carrier's Carriers flag in the VRF.
Added MIB support for graceful restart.

Changed juniBgpVrfOperationalState and juniBgpAddressFamilyOperationalState values to be the same as the values for juniBgpOperationalState. Added support for route-map option in default-information originate and neighbor ... default-originate. Added support for IP profiles and IP service-profiles to be used by BGP when creating IP dynamic interfaces over MPLS tunnels. Added support for new dynamic capability negotiation draft. Added support of passive and promiscuous peers.

Changed juniBgpVrfOperationalState and juniBgpAddressFamilyOperationalState values to be the same as the values for juniBgpOperationalState. Added support for send-label. Added support for carrier's carrier feature for BGP/MPLS VPN. Added support for check-vpn-next-hops.

Changed juniBgpVrfOperationalState and juniBgpAddressFamilyOperationalState values to be the same as the values for juniBgpOperationalState. Added support for maximum-paths eiBGP. Added support for bgpIpV6 to JuniBgpAfi. Replaced VRF distance objects with address family distance objects. Changed default values for VRF maximum paths. Obsoleted storage heap size objects. Added support for leaked flag attribute of the BGP route.

Changed juniBgpVrfOperationalState and juniBgpAddressFamilyOperationalState values to be the same as the values for juniBgpOperationalState. Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names. Added support for neighbor site-of-origin. Added support for juniBgpPeerLenient. Added support for juniBgpPeerGroupLenient. Extended range for maximum paths from 0..6 to 0..16.

Changed juniBgpVrfOperationalState and juniBgpAddressFamilyOperationalState values to be the same as the values for juniBgpOperationalState. Added support for four-octet AS-numbers. Deprecated support for two-octet AS-numbers. Added support for dynamic capability negotiation. Renamed capability objects: juniBgpPeerSupportsCapabilityNegotiation, juniBgpPeerCapabilityMultiProtocol, juniBgpPeerCapabilityRouteRefresh and juniBgpPeerCapabilityRouteRefreshCiscoProprietary to juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilitiesOption, juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityMultiProtocol, juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityRouteRefresh and juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityRouteRefreshCisco respectively. Added support for iBGP multipath. Obsoleted juniBgpEqualCostLimit. Added support for confederation peers filter-list. Added support for juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyMaximumPrefixStrict. Added support for juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyMaximumPrefixStrict. Added support for juniBgpNewRouteMplsInLabel and juniBgpNewRouteMplsOutLabel. Obsoleted juniBgpNewRouteMplsLabel.

Added support for BGP internal redistribute. Obsoleted juniBgpStorageInitialHistoryRoutePoolSize and juniBgpStorageMaxHistoryRoutePoolSize. Added the ability to unconfigure BGP attributes from the MIB.
Added support for adding unicast BGP routes into a multicast view.
Added support for peer and peer-group local-as.

Replaced the route tables to add original route destination as an index: juniBgpRouteTable > juniBgpNewRouteTable juniBgpRouteFlapHistoryTable > juniBgpNewRouteFlapHistoryTable juniBgpRouteCommunityTable > juniBgpNewRouteCommunityTable juniBgpRouteExtendedCommunityTable > juniBgpNewRouteExtendedCommunityTable juniBgpRouteClusterIdTable > juniBgpNewRouteClusterIdTable
Added support for BGP default IPv4 unicast.
Redesigned version of this MIB module.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniBgpMIB.description: The BGP Protocol MIB for the Juniper Networks enterprise.

JuniBgpStorageInteger.name: JuniBgpStorageInteger
JuniBgpStorageInteger.description: Specifies an unsigned integer. If an object with this type is set while BGP is created, the value will not be used until a reboot occurs.

JuniBgpResetConnectionType.name: JuniBgpResetConnectionType
JuniBgpResetConnectionType.description: Writing a value to an object of this type will cause the corresponding reset action to take place: resetTypeNoop - no action (this value is always returned on a read) resetTypeHard - causes a BGP session to be dropped and then re-established resetTypeSoftIn - causes inbound policy to be re-applied to received routes resetTypeSoftOut - causes outbound policy to be re-applied to sent routes resetTypeSoftInOut - does both resetTypeSoftIn and resetTypeSoftOut resetTypeRouteFlapHistory - causes route-flap dampening history to be discarded resetTypeSoftInWithPrefixOrfPush - causes BGP to push out prefix-list ORF and perform inbound soft reconfiguration resetTypeWaitEndOfRib - causes BGP to stop waiting for the End-of-RIB flag from the peer(s) resetTypeRecreateAllIpDynInterfaces - causes all dynamically created IP interfaces to be recreated resetTypeDynamicPeers - causes dynamically create peers to be removed

JuniBgpAdvertiseMapName.name: JuniBgpAdvertiseMapName
JuniBgpAdvertiseMapName.description: Advertise route-map name. Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII character set.
JuniBgpAdvertiseMapName.reference: RFC 854: NVT ASCII character set. See SNMPv2-TC.DisplayString DESCRIPTION for a summary.

juniBgpLocalAsNumber.name: juniBgpLocalAsNumber
juniBgpLocalAsNumber.description: Deprecated. The local autonomous system number. This object has been replaced by juniBgpFourOctetLocalAsNumber. It is still possible to get and set this object, but if the actual local AS number is greater than 65535, getting this object returns 23456 (AS-TRANS).

juniBgpEnabled.name: juniBgpEnabled
juniBgpEnabled.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to have BGP router enabled.

juniBgpIdentifier.name: juniBgpIdentifier
juniBgpIdentifier.description: The BGP identifier of the local system. The identifier is the system router ID by default.

juniBgpAlwaysCompareMed.name: juniBgpAlwaysCompareMed
juniBgpAlwaysCompareMed.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to compare metrics for paths from neighors of different ASs.

juniBgpEqualCostLimit.name: juniBgpEqualCostLimit
juniBgpEqualCostLimit.description: Obsolete maximum equal cost paths to store in the routing table. This object has been replaced by the juniBgpVrfMaximumPathsEbgp object.

juniBgpClientToClientReflection.name: juniBgpClientToClientReflection
juniBgpClientToClientReflection.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to have client-to-client route reflection enabled.

juniBgpClusterId.name: juniBgpClusterId
juniBgpClusterId.description: The cluster ID. When this object is zero, the router ID will be used.

juniBgpConfederationId.name: juniBgpConfederationId
juniBgpConfederationId.description: The confederation ID. When this object is zero, the router is not in a confederation.

juniBgpMissingAsWorst.name: juniBgpMissingAsWorst
juniBgpMissingAsWorst.description: If this object is set to true(1) routes without a MED attribute are considered worse than routes with a MED attribute. If this object is set to false(0) routes without a MED attribute are considered better than routes with a MED attribute.

juniBgpResetAllConnectionType.name: juniBgpResetAllConnectionType
juniBgpResetAllConnectionType.description: Writing a value to this object causes all sessions to all peers to be cleared; the value determines what type of clear is executed (hard clear, soft clear in, soft clear out, etc.). Reading this object has no effect and always returns resetTypeNoop.

juniBgpAdvertiseInactive.name: juniBgpAdvertiseInactive
juniBgpAdvertiseInactive.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to propagate received BGP routes which are not the best route in the IP forwarding table.

juniBgpEnforceFirstAs.name: juniBgpEnforceFirstAs
juniBgpEnforceFirstAs.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to check whether the first AS number in the AS-path in routes from EBGP peers is consistent with the AS number of the peer.

juniBgpConfedCompareMed.name: juniBgpConfedCompareMed
juniBgpConfedCompareMed.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to compare metrics for paths from neighors of different sub-ASs in the same confederation.

juniBgpGlobalRetryInterval.name: juniBgpGlobalRetryInterval
juniBgpGlobalRetryInterval.description: The default number of seconds before BGP retries to establish an outgoing BGP session.

juniBgpGlobalConfigKeepAliveInterval.name: juniBgpGlobalConfigKeepAliveInterval
juniBgpGlobalConfigKeepAliveInterval.description: Default time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer for all peers. Zero means don't send KeepAlive messages.

juniBgpGlobalConfigHoldTime.name: juniBgpGlobalConfigHoldTime
juniBgpGlobalConfigHoldTime.description: Default time interval in seconds for the Hold timer for all peers. Zero means don't expect KeepAlive message to be received.

juniBgpGlobalAsOriginationInterval.name: juniBgpGlobalAsOriginationInterval
juniBgpGlobalAsOriginationInterval.description: Default time interval in seconds for the MinASOriginationInterval timer for all peers.

juniBgpExternalAdvertisementInterval.name: juniBgpExternalAdvertisementInterval
juniBgpExternalAdvertisementInterval.description: Default time interval in seconds for the MinRouteAdvertisementInterval timer for all external peers.

juniBgpGlobalRibOutEnabled.name: juniBgpGlobalRibOutEnabled
juniBgpGlobalRibOutEnabled.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to enable RIB-out by default for all peers, or to false(2) to disable RIB-out by default for all peers.

juniBgpOverloadShutdown.name: juniBgpOverloadShutdown
juniBgpOverloadShutdown.description: Set this object to true(1) for BGP to shut itself down when it runs out of memory. Set this object to false(2) for BGP to continue running (with incomplete information) when it runs out of memory.

juniBgpLogNeighborChanges.name: juniBgpLogNeighborChanges
juniBgpLogNeighborChanges.description: Set this object to true(1) for BGP log a message whenever a peer enters or leaves the established state.

juniBgpFastExternalFallover.name: juniBgpFastExternalFallover
juniBgpFastExternalFallover.description: Set this object to true(1) for BGP to immediately bring down any directly adjacent EBGP session on a link down.

juniBgpInternalAdvertisementInterval.name: juniBgpInternalAdvertisementInterval
juniBgpInternalAdvertisementInterval.description: Default time interval in seconds for the MinRouteAdvertisementInterval timer for all internal peers.

juniBgpMaxAsLimit.name: juniBgpMaxAsLimit
juniBgpMaxAsLimit.description: Maximum length of received AS-path. Received routes with an AS-path longer than this are not placed in the IP forwarding table and are not propagated to other peers. Zero means no maximum length.

juniBgpPreviousOperationalState.name: juniBgpPreviousOperationalState
juniBgpPreviousOperationalState.description: The BGP instance previous operational state.

juniBgpAutomaticRouteTargetFilter.name: juniBgpAutomaticRouteTargetFilter
juniBgpAutomaticRouteTargetFilter.description: Set this object to true(1) for BGP to enable automatic route-target filtering.

juniBgpDefaultIPv4Unicast.name: juniBgpDefaultIPv4Unicast
juniBgpDefaultIPv4Unicast.description: Set this object to true(1) for BGP to automatically activate peers in the IPv4 unicast address family.

juniBgpRedistributeInternal.name: juniBgpRedistributeInternal
juniBgpRedistributeInternal.description: Set this object to true(1) for BGP to automatically redistribute iBGP routes to IGP protocols.

juniBgpFourOctetLocalAsNumber.name: juniBgpFourOctetLocalAsNumber
juniBgpFourOctetLocalAsNumber.description: The four-octet local autonomous system number. This attribute replaces the old two-octet local autonomous system number.

juniBgpConfederationPeersFilterList.name: juniBgpConfederationPeersFilterList
juniBgpConfederationPeersFilterList.description: The confederation peers filter-list contains the name of an as-path access-list. Every neighbor whose remote-AS number matches this as-path access-list is considered a confederation peer. An empty string means that no confederation peers filter-list is configured.

juniBgpUnconfiguredAttributes.name: juniBgpUnconfiguredAttributes
juniBgpUnconfiguredAttributes.description: On get each bit indicates whether the corresponding attribute is configured or unconfigured: 0 = The attribute is configured (i.e. the configured value is the operational value). 1 = The attribute is unconfigured (i.e. the operational value is inherited from the a higher level which could be the default value). Getting the attribute value itself always returns the operational value of that attribute regardless of whether the attribute is configured or unconfigured. On write each bit indicates whether or not the corresponding attribute should be set to the unconfigured state: 0 = No operation (i.e. do not change the state of the attribute). 1 = Set the attribute to the unconfigured state. Setting an attribute to a value has the automatic side-effect of setting the bit with the same name to zero.

juniBgpAdvertiseBestExternalToInternal.name: juniBgpAdvertiseBestExternalToInternal
juniBgpAdvertiseBestExternalToInternal.description: If this object is set to true(1) then BGP advertises the best route received from external (and confederation) peers to internal peers. If this object is set to false(2) then BGP advertises the best route received from all peers to internal peers except if the best route was received from an internal peer in which case BGP doesn't advertise any route to internal peers.

juniBgpGracefulRestartEnabled.name: juniBgpGracefulRestartEnabled
juniBgpGracefulRestartEnabled.description: Set this object to true(1) to enable BGP graceful restart.

juniBgpGracefulRestartRestartTime.name: juniBgpGracefulRestartRestartTime
juniBgpGracefulRestartRestartTime.description: The restart-time advertised in graceful-restart capabilities sent to all peers. This is the estimated time (in seconds) it will take for the BGP session to be re-established after a restart. This can be used to speed up routing convergence by the peer in case that this BGP speaker does not come back after a restart. This value is used by all peers unless overridden by juniBgpPeerGroupGracefulRestartRestartTime or juniBgpPeerGracefulRestartRestartTime.

juniBgpGracefulRestartStalePathsTime.name: juniBgpGracefulRestartStalePathsTime
juniBgpGracefulRestartStalePathsTime.description: The maximum amount of time in seconds we keep stale routes after a session goes down. This value is used for all peers unless it has been overridden by juniBgpPeerGroupGracefulRestartStalePathsTime or juniBgpPeerGracefulRestartStalePathsTime.

juniBgpGracefulRestartPathSelectionDefer.name: juniBgpGracefulRestartPathSelectionDeferTimeLimit
juniBgpGracefulRestartPathSelectionDefer.description: The maximum amount of time in seconds route selection is deferred after a restart.

juniBgpPlatformSupportsNonStopForwarding.name: juniBgpPlatformSupportsNonStopForwarding
juniBgpPlatformSupportsNonStopForwarding.description: Does this platform support non-stop forwarding?

juniBgpDeviceCanPreserveForwardingState.name: juniBgpDeviceCanPreserveForwardingState
juniBgpDeviceCanPreserveForwardingState.description: Is this router at this moment able to do a graceful restart (i.e. is it able to switch over from the primary controller to the standby controller without losing forwarding state on the line cards). The router may not be able to do a graceful restart because the platform does not support non-stop forwarding, because there is no secondary controller present, because the secondary controller is not in standby state, etc.

juniBgpLastRestartWasGraceful.name: juniBgpLastRestartWasGraceful
juniBgpLastRestartWasGraceful.description: Was the most recent restart graceful? (i.e. was forwarding state preserved on the line cards during the most recent switch-over from the primary controller to the standby controller?)

juniBgpBaselineTime.name: juniBgpBaselineTime
juniBgpBaselineTime.description: The sysUpTime at which the counters were most recently baselined.

juniBgpDestinationCount.name: juniBgpDestinationCount
juniBgpDestinationCount.description: Number of distinct destinations in the local RIB.

juniBgpDestinationMemoryUsed.name: juniBgpDestinationMemoryUsed
juniBgpDestinationMemoryUsed.description: Memory used by distinct destinations in the local RIB.

juniBgpRouteCount.name: juniBgpRouteCount
juniBgpRouteCount.description: Number of routes in the local RIB.

juniBgpRouteMemoryUsed.name: juniBgpRouteMemoryUsed
juniBgpRouteMemoryUsed.description: Memory used by routes in the local RIB.

juniBgpSelectedRouteCount.name: juniBgpSelectedRouteCount
juniBgpSelectedRouteCount.description: Number of routes selected for route table installation.

juniBgpPathAttributeCount.name: juniBgpPathAttributeCount
juniBgpPathAttributeCount.description: Number of entries in the path attribute database.

juniBgpPathAttributeMemoryUsed.name: juniBgpPathAttributeMemoryUsed
juniBgpPathAttributeMemoryUsed.description: Memory used by entries in the path attribute database.

juniBgpRouteFlapHistoryCount.name: juniBgpRouteFlapHistoryCount
juniBgpRouteFlapHistoryCount.description: Number of routes with active route flap histories.

juniBgpRouteFlapHistoryMemoryUsed.name: juniBgpRouteFlapHistoryMemoryUsed
juniBgpRouteFlapHistoryMemoryUsed.description: Memory used by routes with active route flap histories.

juniBgpSuppressedRouteCount.name: juniBgpSuppressedRouteCount
juniBgpSuppressedRouteCount.description: Number of routes suppressed due to route flap.

juniBgpConfederationPeerTable.name: juniBgpConfederationPeerTable
juniBgpConfederationPeerTable.description: The Juniper BGP Confederation Peer Table describes the BGP-specific characteristics of confederation peers.

juniBgpConfederationPeerEntry.name: juniBgpConfederationPeerEntry
juniBgpConfederationPeerEntry.description: The BGP Confederation Peer Entry describes BGP-specific characteristics of one confederation peer.

juniBgpConfederationPeerAsNumber.name: juniBgpConfederationPeerAsNumber
juniBgpConfederationPeerAsNumber.description: The AsNumber of this confederation peer.

juniBgpConfederationPeerRowStatus.name: juniBgpConfederationPeerRowStatus
juniBgpConfederationPeerRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy

juniBgpFourOctetConfederationPeerTable.name: juniBgpFourOctetConfederationPeerTable
juniBgpFourOctetConfederationPeerTable.description: The BGP New Confederation Peer Table describes the BGP-specific characteristics of confederation peers using four-octet AS-numbers.

juniBgpFourOctetConfederationPeerEntry.name: juniBgpFourOctetConfederationPeerEntry
juniBgpFourOctetConfederationPeerEntry.description: The BGP New Confederation Peer Entry describes BGP-specific characteristics of one confederation peer using four-octet AS-numbers.

juniBgpFourOctetConfederationPeerAsNumbe.name: juniBgpFourOctetConfederationPeerAsNumber
juniBgpFourOctetConfederationPeerAsNumbe.description: The four-octet AS-number of this confederation peer.

juniBgpFourOctetConfederationPeerRowStat.name: juniBgpFourOctetConfederationPeerRowStatus
juniBgpFourOctetConfederationPeerRowStat.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy

juniBgpPeerTable.name: juniBgpPeerTable
juniBgpPeerTable.description: The Juniper BGP Peer Table describes the BGP-specific characteristics of peers.

juniBgpPeerEntry.name: juniBgpPeerEntry
juniBgpPeerEntry.description: The BGP Peer Entry describes BGP-specific characteristics of one peer.

juniBgpPeerVrfName.name: juniBgpPeerVrfName
juniBgpPeerVrfName.description: The name of the VPN Routing Forwarding (VRF) instance in which this peer is configured. The empty string indicates that this peer is not in a VRF.

juniBgpPeerRemoteAddress.name: juniBgpPeerRemoteAddress
juniBgpPeerRemoteAddress.description: The remote IP address of this entry's BGP peer.

juniBgpPeerAdminStatus.name: juniBgpPeerAdminStatus
juniBgpPeerAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the BGP connection. A transition from 'stop' to 'start' will cause the BGP Start Event to be generated. A transition from 'start' to 'stop' will cause the BGP Stop Event to be generated. This parameter can be used to restart BGP peer connections. Care should be used in providing write access to this object without adequate authentication.

juniBgpPeerNegotiatedVersion.name: juniBgpPeerNegotiatedVersion
juniBgpPeerNegotiatedVersion.description: The negotiated version of BGP running between the two peers.

juniBgpPeerLocalAddress.name: juniBgpPeerLocalAddress
juniBgpPeerLocalAddress.description: The local IP address of this entry's BGP connection.

juniBgpPeerLocalAddressMask.name: juniBgpPeerLocalAddressMask
juniBgpPeerLocalAddressMask.description: The local IP address mask of this entry's BGP connection.

juniBgpPeerLocalPort.name: juniBgpPeerLocalPort
juniBgpPeerLocalPort.description: The local port for the TCP connection between the BGP peers.

juniBgpPeerRemoteAsNumber.name: juniBgpPeerRemoteAsNumber
juniBgpPeerRemoteAsNumber.description: Deprecated. The peer's autonomous system number. This object has been replaced by juniBgpPeerFourOctetRemoteAsNumber. It is still possible to get and set this object, but if the actual remote AS number is greater than 65535, getting this object returns 23456 (AS-TRANS).

juniBgpPeerRemotePort.name: juniBgpPeerRemotePort
juniBgpPeerRemotePort.description: The remote port for the TCP connection between the BGP peers. Note that the objects bgpPeerLocalAddr, bgpPeerLocalPort, bgpPeerRemoteAddr and bgpPeerRemotePort provide the appropriate reference to the standard MIB TCP connection table.

juniBgpPeerInUpdates.name: juniBgpPeerInUpdates
juniBgpPeerInUpdates.description: The number of BGP UPDATE messages received on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero (0) when the connection is established.

juniBgpPeerOutUpdates.name: juniBgpPeerOutUpdates
juniBgpPeerOutUpdates.description: The number of BGP UPDATE messages transmitted on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero (0) when the connection is established.

juniBgpPeerInTotalMessages.name: juniBgpPeerInTotalMessages
juniBgpPeerInTotalMessages.description: The total number of messages received from the remote peer on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

juniBgpPeerOutTotalMessages.name: juniBgpPeerOutTotalMessages
juniBgpPeerOutTotalMessages.description: The total number of messages transmitted to the remote peer on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

juniBgpPeerLastErrorCode.name: juniBgpPeerLastErrorCode
juniBgpPeerLastErrorCode.description: The last error code and subcode seen by this peer on this connection. If no error has occurred, this field is zero. Otherwise, the first byte of this two byte OCTET STRING contains the error code, and the second byte contains the subcode.

juniBgpPeerLastResetReason.name: juniBgpPeerLastResetReason
juniBgpPeerLastResetReason.description: The string representing the last error code seen by this peer on this connection. If no error has occurred, this string is null.

juniBgpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions.name: juniBgpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions
juniBgpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions.description: The total number of times the BGP FSM transitioned into the established state.

juniBgpPeerFsmEstablishedTime.name: juniBgpPeerFsmEstablishedTime
juniBgpPeerFsmEstablishedTime.description: This timer indicates how long (in seconds) this peer has been in the Established state or how long since this peer was last in the Established state. It is set to zero when a new peer is configured or the router is booted.

juniBgpPeerRetryInterval.name: juniBgpPeerRetryInterval
juniBgpPeerRetryInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the ConnectRetry timer. The suggested value for this timer is 120 seconds.

juniBgpPeerHoldTime.name: juniBgpPeerHoldTime
juniBgpPeerHoldTime.description: Time interval in seconds for the Hold Timer established with the peer. The value of this object is calculated by this BGP speaker by using the smaller of the value in bgpPeerHoldTimeConfigured and the Hold Time received in the OPEN message. This value must be at lease three seconds if it is not zero (0) in which case the Hold Timer has not been established with the peer, or, the value of bgpPeerHoldTimeConfigured is zero (0).

juniBgpPeerKeepAliveInterval.name: juniBgpPeerKeepAliveInterval
juniBgpPeerKeepAliveInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer established with the peer. The value of this object is calculated by this BGP speaker such that, when compared with bgpPeerHoldTime, it has the same proportion as what bgpPeerKeepAliveConfigured has when compared with bgpPeerHoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), it indicates that the KeepAlive timer has not been established with the peer, or, the value of bgpPeerKeepAliveConfigured is zero (0).

juniBgpPeerConfigHoldTime.name: juniBgpPeerConfigHoldTime
juniBgpPeerConfigHoldTime.description: Time interval in seconds for the Hold Time configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. This value is placed in an OPEN message sent to this peer by this BGP speaker, and is compared with the Hold Time field in an OPEN message received from the peer when determining the Hold Time (bgpPeerHoldTime) with the peer. This value must not be less than three seconds if it is not zero (0) in which case the Hold Time is NOT to be established with the peer. The suggested value for this timer is 90 seconds.

juniBgpPeerConfigKeepAliveInterval.name: juniBgpPeerConfigKeepAliveInterval
juniBgpPeerConfigKeepAliveInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. The value of this object will only determine the KEEPALIVE messages' frequency relative to the value specified in bgpPeerHoldTimeConfigured; the actual time interval for the KEEPALIVE messages is indicated by bgpPeerKeepAlive. A reasonable maximum value for this timer would be configured to be one third of that of bgpPeerHoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), no periodical KEEPALIVE messages are sent to the peer after the BGP connection has been established. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

juniBgpPeerAsOriginationInterval.name: juniBgpPeerAsOriginationInterval
juniBgpPeerAsOriginationInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinASOriginationInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 10 seconds.

juniBgpPeerAdvertisementInterval.name: juniBgpPeerAdvertisementInterval
juniBgpPeerAdvertisementInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinRouteAdvertisementInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

juniBgpPeerInUpdateElapsedTime.name: juniBgpPeerInUpdateElapsedTime
juniBgpPeerInUpdateElapsedTime.description: Elapsed time in seconds since the last BGP UPDATE message was received from the peer. Each time bgpPeerInUpdates is incremented, the value of this object is set to zero (0).

juniBgpPeerWeight.name: juniBgpPeerWeight
juniBgpPeerWeight.description: The weight assigned to routes learned from peer.

juniBgpPeerEbgpMultihopTtl.name: juniBgpPeerEbgpMultihopTtl
juniBgpPeerEbgpMultihopTtl.description: Maximum number of hops to the external peer (only relevant if EBGP multihop turned on).

juniBgpPeerUpdateSource.name: juniBgpPeerUpdateSource
juniBgpPeerUpdateSource.description: The source IP address for peer connections.

juniBgpPeerMd5Password.name: juniBgpPeerMd5Password
juniBgpPeerMd5Password.description: The password for MD5 authentication. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero.

juniBgpPeerMaxUpdateSize.name: juniBgpPeerMaxUpdateSize
juniBgpPeerMaxUpdateSize.description: The maximum size in bytes of transmitted UPDATE messages.

juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilitiesOption.name: juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilitiesOption
juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilitiesOption.description: The peer sent the capabilities optional parameter in its open message.

juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityMultiProtoc.name: juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityMultiProtocol
juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityMultiProtoc.description: The peer has advertised the multi-protocol capability to us.

juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityRouteRefres.name: juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityRouteRefresh
juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityRouteRefres.description: The peer has advertised the route-refresh capability to us.

juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityRouteRefres.name: juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityRouteRefreshCisco
juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityRouteRefres.description: The peer has advertised the route-refresh-cisco capability to us.

juniBgpPeerResetConnectionType.name: juniBgpPeerResetConnectionType
juniBgpPeerResetConnectionType.description: Writing a value to this object causes the session to the peer to be cleared; the value determines what type of clear is executed (hard clear, soft clear in, soft clear out, etc.). Reading this object has no effect and always returns resetTypeNoop.

juniBgpPeerRowStatus.name: juniBgpPeerRowStatus
juniBgpPeerRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy

juniBgpPeerLocalAsNumber.name: juniBgpPeerLocalAsNumber
juniBgpPeerLocalAsNumber.description: Deprecated. The local autonomous system number to be used for this peer. Value zero (0) means that the global local automous system number (as specified in the object juniBgpPeerLocalAsNumber) is used. This object has been replaced by juniBgpPeerFourOctetLocalAsNumber. It is still possible to get and set this object, but if the actual local AS number is greater than 65535, getting this object returns AS-TRANS (23456).

juniBgpPeerFourOctetRemoteAsNumber.name: juniBgpPeerFourOctetRemoteAsNumber
juniBgpPeerFourOctetRemoteAsNumber.description: The peer's four-octet autonomous system number.

juniBgpPeerFourOctetLocalAsNumber.name: juniBgpPeerFourOctetLocalAsNumber
juniBgpPeerFourOctetLocalAsNumber.description: The four-octet local autonomous system number to be used for this peer. Value zero (0) means that the global local automous system number (as specified in the object juniBgpPeerFourOctetLocalAsNumber) is used.

juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityFourOctetAs.name: juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityFourOctetAsNumbers
juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityFourOctetAs.description: The peer has advertised the four-octet-as-numbers capability to us.

juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityDynamicCapa.name: juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityDynamicCapabilityNeg
juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityDynamicCapa.description: The peer has advertised the dynamic-capability-negotiation capability to us.

juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilitiesOp.name: juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilitiesOption
juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilitiesOp.description: Set this object to true if the capabilities option should be included in OPEN messages sent to this peer. Even if this object is set to true, BGP may decide not to include the capabilities option in OPEN messages sent to this peer (for example when it is detected that the peer does not support capability negotiation). The juniBgpPeerSentCapabilitiesOption can be used to determine whether or not the OPEN message sent to the peer actually contained the capabilities option.

juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityRout.name: juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityRouteRefresh
juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityRout.description: Set this object to true if the route-refresh capability should be advertised to this peer. Even if this object is set to true, BGP may decide not to advertise the route-refresh capability to this peer (for example when it is detected that the peer does not support capability negotiation or when it is detected that the peer does not support the route-refresh capability and incorrectly sends an unsupported capability notification). The juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityRouteRefresh can be used to determine whether or not the capability was actually advertised to the peer.

juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityRout.name: juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityRouteRefreshCisco
juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityRout.description: Set this object to true if the route-refresh-cisco capability should be advertised to this peer. Even if this object is set to true, BGP may decide not to advertise the route-refresh-cisco capability to this peer (for example when it is detected that the peer does not support capability negotiation or when it is detected that the peer does not support the route-refresh-cisco capability and incorrectly sends an unsupported capability notification). The juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityRouteRefreshCisco can be used to determine whether or not the capability was actually advertised to the peer.

juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityFour.name: juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityFourOctetAsNumbers
juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityFour.description: Set this object to true if the four-octet-as-numbers capability should be advertised to this peer. Even if this object is set to true, BGP may decide not to advertise the four-octet-as-numbers capability to this peer (for example when it is detected that the peer does not support capability negotiation or when it is detected that the peer does not support the four-octet-as-numbers capability and incorrectly sends an unsupported capability notification). The juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityFourOctetAsNumbers can be used to determine whether or not the capability was actually advertised to the peer.

juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityDyna.name: juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityDynamicCapabilityNeg
juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityDyna.description: Set this object to true if the dynamic-capability-negotiation capability should be advertised to this peer. Even if this object is set to true, BGP may decide not to advertise the dynamic-capability-negotiation capability to this peer (for example when it is detected that the peer does not support capability negotiation or when it is detected that the peer does not support the dynamic-capability-negotiation capability and incorrectly sends an unsupported capability notification). The juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityDynamicCapabilityNeg can be used to determine whether or not the capability was actually advertised to the peer.

juniBgpPeerSentCapabilitiesOption.name: juniBgpPeerSentCapabilitiesOption
juniBgpPeerSentCapabilitiesOption.description: We sent the capabilities optional parameter in the OPEN message to this peer.

juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityMultiProtocol.name: juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityMultiProtocol
juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityMultiProtocol.description: We advertised the multi-protocol capability to this peer.

juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityRouteRefresh.name: juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityRouteRefresh
juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityRouteRefresh.description: We advertised the route-refresh capability to this peer.

juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityRouteRefreshCis.name: juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityRouteRefreshCisco
juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityRouteRefreshCis.description: We advertised the route-refresh-cisco capability to this peer.

juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityFourOctetAsNumb.name: juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityFourOctetAsNumbers
juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityFourOctetAsNumb.description: We advertised the four-octet-as-numbers capability to this peer.

juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityDynamicCapabili.name: juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityDynamicCapabilityNeg
juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityDynamicCapabili.description: We advertised the dynamic-capability-negotiation capability to this peer.

juniBgpPeerReceivedUnsupportedOptionalPa.name: juniBgpPeerReceivedUnsupportedOptionalParameterNotification
juniBgpPeerReceivedUnsupportedOptionalPa.description: We received an unsupported optional parameter notification from this peer. This indicates that the peer does not support capability negotiation. When this object is set to true, we do not include the capabilities optional parameter in OPEN messages sent to this peer. A hard clear of the session is needed to retry sending the capabilities optional parameter.

juniBgpPeerReceivedUnsupportedCapability.name: juniBgpPeerReceivedUnsupportedCapabilityNotification
juniBgpPeerReceivedUnsupportedCapability.description: We received an unsupported capability notification from this peer. This often happens because the peer did not recognize a capability which we advertised to the peer and that peer incorrectly send back an unsupported capability notification (the peer should ignore the unsupported capability instead). When this object is set to true, we do not advertise capabilities that the peer does not support.

juniBgpPeerUnconfiguredAttributes.name: juniBgpPeerUnconfiguredAttributes
juniBgpPeerUnconfiguredAttributes.description: On get each bit indicates whether the corresponding attribute is configured or unconfigured: 0 = The attribute is configured (i.e. the configured value is the operational value). 1 = The attribute is unconfigured (i.e. the operational value is inherited from the a higher level which could be the default value). Getting the attribute value itself always returns the operational value of that attribute regardless of whether the attribute is configured or unconfigured. On write each bit indicates whether or not the corresponding attribute should be set to the unconfigured state: 0 = No operation (i.e. do not change the state of the attribute). 1 = Set the attribute to the unconfigured state. Setting an attribute to a value has the automatic side-effect of setting the bit with the same name to zero.

juniBgpPeerSiteOfOrigin.name: juniBgpPeerSiteOfOrigin
juniBgpPeerSiteOfOrigin.description: The site-of-origin. This site-of-origin is added to the extended communities for all routes received from the peer. When sending routes to this peer all routes with this extended community are filtered. The null extended community (all 8 bytes zero) means that no site-of-origin is configured for this peer. It is not allowed to set this object to any extended community other than a site-of-origin type of extended community or null.

juniBgpPeerLenient.name: juniBgpPeerLenient
juniBgpPeerLenient.description: Enable Lenient behavior for this peer so that it is more tolerant of finite state machine errors and malformed messages received from the remote peer and avoids terminating the peer session whenever possible.

juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityOldDynamicC.name: juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityOldDynamicCapabilityNeg
juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityOldDynamicC.description: The peer has advertised the old deprecated dynamic-capability- negotiation capability to us.

juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityOldD.name: juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityOldDynamicCapabilityNeg
juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityOldD.description: Set this object to true if the deprecated-dynamic-capability- negotiation capability should be advertised to this peer. Even if this object is set to true, BGP may decide not to advertise the deprecated-dynamic-capability-negotiation capability to this peer (for example when it is detected that the peer does not support capability negotiation or when it is detected that the peer does not support the deprecated-dynamic-capability-negotiation capability and incorrectly sends an unsupported capability notification). The juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityOldDynamicCapabilityNeg can be used to determine whether or not the capability was actually advertised to the peer.

juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityOldDynamicCapab.name: juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityOldDynamicCapabilityNeg
juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityOldDynamicCapab.description: We advertised the old-dynamic-capability-negotiation capability to this peer.

juniBgpPeerPassive.name: juniBgpPeerPassive
juniBgpPeerPassive.description: Set this object to true(1) to make this a passive peer.

juniBgpPeerDynamic.name: juniBgpPeerDynamic
juniBgpPeerDynamic.description: This object return true(1) if this is a dynamically created peer or false(2) if this is a configured peer.

juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityGrac.name: juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityGracefulRestart
juniBgpPeerShouldAdvertiseCapabilityGrac.description: Set this object to true if the graceful-restart capability should be advertised to all peers. Even if this object is set to true, BGP may decide not to advertise the graceful-restart capability to a peer (for example when graceful-restart is not enabled or when it is detected that the peer does not support capability negotiation). The juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityGracefulRestart can be used to determine whether or not the capability was actually advertised to the peer.

juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityGracefulRestart.name: juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityGracefulRestart
juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityGracefulRestart.description: We advertised the graceful-restart capability to this peer.

juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityGracefulRes.name: juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityGracefulRestart
juniBgpPeerReceivedCapabilityGracefulRes.description: The peer has advertised the graceful-restart capability to us.

juniBgpPeerGracefulRestartRestartTime.name: juniBgpPeerGracefulRestartRestartTime
juniBgpPeerGracefulRestartRestartTime.description: The restart-time advertised in the graceful-restart capability sent to this peer. This is the estimated time (in seconds) it will take for the BGP session to be re-established after a restart. This can be used to speed up routing convergence by the peer in case that this BGP speaker does not come back after a restart. This value (if configured) overrides the global value configured in juniBgpGracefulRestartRestartTime and the value for the peer-group configured in juniBgpPeerGroupGracefulRestartRestartTime.

juniBgpPeerGracefulRestartStalePathsTime.name: juniBgpPeerGracefulRestartStalePathsTime
juniBgpPeerGracefulRestartStalePathsTime.description: The maximum amount of time in seconds we keep stale routes after the session to this peer goes down. This value (if configured) overrides the global value configured in juniBgpGracefulRestartStalePathsTime and the value for the peer-group configured in juniBgpPeerGroupGracefulRestartStalePathsTime.

juniBgpPeerSentGracefulRestartRestartSta.name: juniBgpPeerSentGracefulRestartRestartState
juniBgpPeerSentGracefulRestartRestartSta.description: Value true(1) indicates that the OPEN message most recently sent to this peer contained the graceful-restart capability with the Restart-State (R) bit in the Restart Flags field set to one (this indicates that BGP has experienced a restart).

juniBgpPeerReceivedGracefulRestartRestar.name: juniBgpPeerReceivedGracefulRestartRestartState
juniBgpPeerReceivedGracefulRestartRestar.description: Value true(1) indicates that the OPEN message most recently received from this peer contained the graceful-restart capability with the Restart-State (R) bit in the Restart Flags field set to one (this indicates that the peer has experienced a restart).

juniBgpPeerSentGracefulRestartRestartTim.name: juniBgpPeerSentGracefulRestartRestartTime
juniBgpPeerSentGracefulRestartRestartTim.description: The restart time in seconds field in the graceful-restart capability which we sent to the peer.

juniBgpPeerReceivedGracefulRestartRestar.name: juniBgpPeerReceivedGracefulRestartRestartTime
juniBgpPeerReceivedGracefulRestartRestar.description: The restart time in seconds field in the graceful-restart capability which we received from the peer.

juniBgpPeerTimeUntilGracefulRestartResta.name: juniBgpPeerTimeUntilGracefulRestartRestartTimerExpires
juniBgpPeerTimeUntilGracefulRestartResta.description: If the restart-timer is running this object contains the number of seconds before it will expire. If the restart-timer is not running this object contains zero. The restart-timer is used to limit the amount of time that we are willing to wait for the session to come back up after the peer restarts.

juniBgpPeerTimeUntilGracefulRestartStale.name: juniBgpPeerTimeUntilGracefulRestartStalePathsTimerExpires
juniBgpPeerTimeUntilGracefulRestartStale.description: If the stale-paths-timer is running this object contains the number of seconds before it will expire. If the stale-paths-timer is not running this object contains zero. The stale-paths-timer is used to limit the amount of time that we are willing continue using stale routes from a peer after that peer restarts.

juniBgpPeerBfdEnabled.name: juniBgpPeerBfdEnabled
juniBgpPeerBfdEnabled.description: Value true(1) the BFD is enabled for this peer.

juniBgpPeerBfdMinTransmitInterval.name: juniBgpPeerBfdMinTransmitInterval
juniBgpPeerBfdMinTransmitInterval.description: The minimum interval (in milliseconds) between BFD packets sent to the remote BFD speaker. In other words, it specifies the maximum rate at which we are willing to send BFD packets.

juniBgpPeerBfdMinReceiveInterval.name: juniBgpPeerBfdMinReceiveInterval
juniBgpPeerBfdMinReceiveInterval.description: The minimum interval (in milliseconds) between BFD packets received from the remote BFD speaker. In other words, it specifies the maximum rate at which we are willing to receive BFD packets.

juniBgpPeerBfdMultiplier.name: juniBgpPeerBfdMultiplier
juniBgpPeerBfdMultiplier.description: How many BFD packets can be missed before the BFD session is declared down.

juniBgpPeerBfdDetectionTime.name: juniBgpPeerBfdDetectionTime
juniBgpPeerBfdDetectionTime.description: The BFD detection time (in milliseconds) negotiated with the remote BFD speaker. In other words, how quickly can a broken connection be detected.

juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerTable.name: juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerTable
juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerTable.description: The Juniper BGP PeerProposedAfiSafi Peer Table describes the BGP-specific AFI and SAFIs a peer proposed.

juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerEntry.name: juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerEntry
juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerEntry.description: The BGP PeerProposedAfiSafi Peer Entry describes a BGP-specific AFI/SAFIs proposed by one peer.

juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerVrfName.name: juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerVrfName
juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerVrfName.description: The name of the VPN Routing Forwarding (VRF) instance in which this peer is configured. The empty string indicates that this peer is not in a VRF.

juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerRemoteAddr.name: juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerRemoteAddr
juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerRemoteAddr.description: The remote IP address of this entry's BGP peer.

juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerAfi.name: juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerAfi
juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerAfi.description: The AFI proposed by this peer to us.

juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerSafi.name: juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerSafi
juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerSafi.description: The SAFI proposed by this peer to us.

juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerRowStatus.name: juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerRowStatus
juniBgpPeerProposedAfiSafiPeerRowStatus.description: Should always be active according to the Row Status convention.

juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerTable.name: juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerTable
juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerTable.description: The Juniper BGP LocalProposedAfiSafi Peer Table describes the BGP-specific AFI and SAFIs proposed to the peer.

juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerEntry.name: juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerEntry
juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerEntry.description: The BGP LocalProposedAfiSafi Peer Entry describes a BGP-specific AFI/SAFIs proposed to one peer.

juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerVrfName.name: juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerVrfName
juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerVrfName.description: The name of the VPN Routing Forwarding (VRF) instance in which this peer is configured. The empty string indicates that this peer is not in a VRF.

juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerRemoteAdd.name: juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerRemoteAddr
juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerRemoteAdd.description: The remote IP address of this entry's BGP peer.

juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerAfi.name: juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerAfi
juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerAfi.description: The AFI we proposed to this peer.

juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerSafi.name: juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerSafi
juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerSafi.description: The SAFI we proposed to this peer.

juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerRowStatus.name: juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerRowStatus
juniBgpLocalProposedAfiSafiPeerRowStatus.description: Should always be active according to the Row Status convention.

juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerTable.name: juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerTable
juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerTable.description: The Juniper BGP PeerExchangedAfiSafi Peer Table describes the BGP-specific AFI and SAFIs a peer exchanged.

juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerEntry.name: juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerEntry
juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerEntry.description: The BGP ExchangedAfiSafi Peer Entry describes a BGP-specific AFI/SAFIs exchanged by one peer.

juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerVrfName.name: juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerVrfName
juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerVrfName.description: The name of the VPN Routing Forwarding (VRF) instance in which this peer is configured. The empty string indicates that this peer is not in a VRF.

juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerRemoteAddr.name: juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerRemoteAddr
juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerRemoteAddr.description: The remote IP address of this entry's BGP peer.

juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerAfi.name: juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerAfi
juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerAfi.description: The AFI which we exchange with this peer.

juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerSafi.name: juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerSafi
juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerSafi.description: The SAFI which we exchange with this peer.

juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerRowStatus.name: juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerRowStatus
juniBgpExchangedAfiSafiPeerRowStatus.description: Should always be active according to the Row Status convention.

juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityTable.name: juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityTable
juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityTable.description: The BGP PeerDynamicCapbility Table describes which dynamic capbilities we proposed to the peer, which the peer proposed to us, and which are being used.

juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityEntry.name: juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityEntry
juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityEntry.description: The BGP PeerDynamicCapbility Entry describes one dynamic capability.

juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityPeerVrfName.name: juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityPeerVrfName
juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityPeerVrfName.description: The name of the VPN Routing Forwarding (VRF) instance in which this peer is configured. The empty string indicates that this peer is not in a VRF.

juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityPeerRemoteAd.name: juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityPeerRemoteAddr
juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityPeerRemoteAd.description: The remote IP address of this entry's BGP peer.

juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityCode.name: juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityCode
juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityCode.description: The capability code for the dynamic capability.

juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilitySent.name: juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilitySent
juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilitySent.description: Returns true if we advertised capability code juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityCode in the dynamic-capability-negotiation capability which we sent to this peer.

juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityReceived.name: juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityReceived
juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityReceived.description: Returns true if the peer advertised capability code juniBgpPeerDynamicCapabilityCode in the dynamic-capability-negotiation capability which this peer sent to us.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyTable.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyTable
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyTable.description: The Juniper BGP Peer Address Family Table describes the BGP-specific attributes of an Address Family for a peer.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyEntry.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyEntry
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyEntry.description: The BGP ExchangedAfiSafi Peer Entry describes a BGP-specific AFI/SAFIs exchanged by one peer.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyVrfName.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyVrfName
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyVrfName.description: The name of the VPN Routing Forwarding (VRF) instance in which this peer is configured. The empty string indicates that this peer is not in a VRF.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAfi.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAfi
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAfi.description: The AFI of the address-family in which this peer is configured.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySafi.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySafi
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySafi.description: The SAFI of the address-family in which this peer is configured.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRemoteAddress.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRemoteAddress
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRemoteAddress.description: The remote IP address of this entry's BGP peer.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyDefaultOriginate.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyDefaultOriginate
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyDefaultOriginate.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to advertise a default route to this peer, if present.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyNextHopSelf.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyNextHopSelf
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyNextHopSelf.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to always advertise this router as the next hop.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySendCommunity.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySendCommunity
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySendCommunity.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to send COMMUNITIES attributes in updates.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyDistributeListIn.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyDistributeListIn
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyDistributeListIn.description: The inbound distribute IP access list name.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyDistributeListOu.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyDistributeListOut
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyDistributeListOu.description: The outbound distribute IP access list name.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyPrefixListIn.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyPrefixListIn
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyPrefixListIn.description: The inbound IP prefix list name.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyPrefixListOut.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyPrefixListOut
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyPrefixListOut.description: The outbound IP prefix list name.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyPrefixTreeIn.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyPrefixTreeIn
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyPrefixTreeIn.description: The inbound IP prefix tree name.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyPrefixTreeOut.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyPrefixTreeOut
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyPrefixTreeOut.description: The outbound IP prefix tree name.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyFilterListIn.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyFilterListIn
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyFilterListIn.description: The inbound filter AS path list name.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyFilterListOut.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyFilterListOut
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyFilterListOut.description: The outbound filter AS path list name.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyFilterListWeight.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyFilterListWeight
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyFilterListWeight.description: The weight filter AS path list name.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyFilterListWeight.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyFilterListWeightValue
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyFilterListWeight.description: The weight to apply on weight filter list matches.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteMapIn.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteMapIn
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteMapIn.description: The inbound route-map name. An empty string means no inbound route-map.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteMapOut.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteMapOut
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteMapOut.description: The outbound route-map name. An empty string means no outbound route-map.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteReflectorCl.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteReflectorClient
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteReflectorCl.description: The peer is a route reflector client.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteLimitWarn.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteLimitWarn
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteLimitWarn.description: Log a warning if pathCount exceeds this value.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteLimitReset.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteLimitReset
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteLimitReset.description: Reset connection is pathCount exceeds this value.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteLimitWarnOn.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteLimitWarnOnly
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteLimitWarnOn.description: Warn, but do not reset, if the path limit is exceeded.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRemovePrivateAs.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRemovePrivateAs
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRemovePrivateAs.description: Remove private AS numbers from AS paths.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyUnsuppressMap.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyUnsuppressMap
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyUnsuppressMap.description: The unsuppress route-map name. Routes which are sent to this peer and which match this route-map are not subject to suppression by summary-only aggregates. An empty string means no unsuppress route-map.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyInboundSoftRecon.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyInboundSoftReconfig
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyInboundSoftRecon.description: Inbound soft-reconfiguration is enabled. If inbound soft-reconfiguration is enabled we keep a copy of each received route before inbound policy was applied.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyResetConnectionT.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyResetConnectionType
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyResetConnectionT.description: Writing a value to this object causes one individual address family within the session to the peer to be cleared; the value determines what type of clear is executed (hard clear, soft clear in, soft clear out, etc.). Note that hard clearing an address family within a session will bounce the session and thus also affect the other address families in the session. Reading this object has no effect and always returns resetTypeNoop.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRowStatus.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRowStatus
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAsOverride.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAsOverride
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAsOverride.description: Replace the AS number of the peer by our own AS number in the AS-path attribute in UPDATEs sent to this peer.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAllowAsIn.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAllowAsIn
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAllowAsIn.description: The maximum number of times our own AS number is allowed to occur in a received AS-path before that received route is considered to be a loop and therefore rejected.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySendExtendedComm.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySendExtendedCommunity
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySendExtendedComm.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to send EXTENDED-COMMUNITIES attributes in updates.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPref.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPrefixListOrfSend
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPref.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to send PREFIX-LIST ORF SEND CAPABILITY in Open Message.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPref.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPrefixListOrfReceive
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPref.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to send PREFIX-LIST ORF RECEIVE CAPABILITY in Open Message.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPref.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPrefixListCiscoOrfSend
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPref.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to send PREFIX-LIST-CISCO ORF SEND CAPABILITY in Open Message.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPref.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPrefixListCiscoOrfReceive
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPref.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to send PREFIX-LIST-CISCO ORF RECEIVE CAPABILITY in Open Message.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapPrefi.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapPrefixListOrfSend
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapPrefi.description: The peer has sent PREFIX-LIST ORF SEND CAPABILITY to us for this address family.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapPrefi.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapPrefixListOrfReceive
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapPrefi.description: The peer has sent PREFIX-LIST ORF RECEIVE CAPABILITY to us for this address family.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapPrefi.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapPrefixListCiscoOrfSend
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapPrefi.description: The peer has sent PREFIX-LIST-CISCO ORF SEND CAPABILITY to us for this address family.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapPrefi.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapPrefixListCiscoOrfReceive
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapPrefi.description: The peer has sent PREFIX-LIST-CISCO ORF RECEIVE CAPABILITY to us for this address family.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedOrfEntri.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedOrfEntriesLimit
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedOrfEntri.description: Ignore received ORF entries for this address family if count exceeds this value.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedPrefixLi.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedPrefixListOrfName
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedPrefixLi.description: The prefix list name containing ORF entries received from the peer for this address family

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyMaximumPrefixStr.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyMaximumPrefixStrict
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyMaximumPrefixStr.description: If the juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyInboundSoftReconfig object is set to true then routes which were rejected by inbound policy are stored in memory anyway. The juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyMaximumPrefixStrict object determines whether or not these routes count towards the maximum number of routes from the peer (as configured in juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteLimitWarn and/or juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyRouteLimitReset).

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyUnconfiguredAttr.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyUnconfiguredAttributes
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyUnconfiguredAttr.description: On get each bit indicates whether the corresponding attribute is configured or unconfigured: 0 = The attribute is configured (i.e. the configured value is the operational value). 1 = The attribute is unconfigured (i.e. the operational value is inherited from the a higher level which could be the default value). Getting the attribute value itself always returns the operational value of that attribute regardless of whether the attribute is configured or unconfigured. On write each bit indicates whether or not the corresponding attribute should be set to the unconfigured state: 0 = No operation (i.e. do not change the state of the attribute). 1 = Set the attribute to the unconfigured state. Setting an attribute to a value has the automatic side-effect of setting the bit with the same name to zero.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySendLabel.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySendLabel
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySendLabel.description: Send labeled prefixes to this peer for this address-family.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyDefaultOriginate.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyDefaultOriginateRouteMap
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyDefaultOriginate.description: The route-map to apply to the default route which is advertised to this peer as a result of setting juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyDefaultOriginate to true. An empty string means that no route-map is applied.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySentCapabilityGr.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySentCapabilityGracefulRestart
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySentCapabilityGr.description: Value true(1) means that an AFI-SAFI block for this address-family was included in the graceful-restart capability which we sent to this peer.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapabili.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapabilityGracefulRestart
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedCapabili.description: Value true(1) means that an AFI-SAFI block for this address-family was included in the graceful-restart capability which we received from this peer.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySentForwardingSt.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySentForwardingStatePreserved
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySentForwardingSt.description: Value true(1) indicates that the OPEN message most recently sent to this peer contained the graceful-restart capability which included an AFI-SAFI block for this address-family with the Forwarding-State (F) bit in the Flags for Address Family field set to one (this indicates that forwarding state has been preserved for the address family during the previous restart).

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedForwardi.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedForwardingStatePreserved
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedForwardi.description: Value true(1) indicates that the OPEN message most recently received from this peer contained the graceful-restart capability which included an AFI-SAFI block for this address-family with the Forwarding-State (F) bit in the Flags for Address Family field set to one (this indicates that the peer preserved forwarding state for the address family during the previous restart).

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySentEndOfRibMark.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySentEndOfRibMarker
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilySentEndOfRibMark.description: Value true(1) indicates that we have sent an End-of-RIB marker for this address-family to this peer since the session became established.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedEndOfRib.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedEndOfRibMarker
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyReceivedEndOfRib.description: Value true(1) indicates that we have received an End-of-RIB marker for this address-family from this peer since the session became established.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyWaitingForEndOfR.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyWaitingForEndOfRibBeforeFlushStaleRoutes
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyWaitingForEndOfR.description: Value true(1) indicates that we are still waiting for an End-of-RIB marker from this peer before flushing all remaining stale routes from the address-family.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyWaitingForEndOfR.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyWaitingForEndOfRibBeforePathSelection
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyWaitingForEndOfR.description: Value true(1) indicates that we are still waiting for an End-of-RIB marker from this peer before we stop deferring path selection for this address-family.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyNextHopUnchanged.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyNextHopUnchanged
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyNextHopUnchanged.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to always advertise the the next-hop unchanged to this peer for this address-family.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvTa.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvTable
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvTa.description: The Juniper BGP Peer Address Family Conditional Advertisement Table describes the BGP conditional advertisement attributes in an Address Family for a peer.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvEn.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvEntry
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvEn.description: The Juniper BGP Peer Address Family Conditional Advertisement Entry describes a specific conditional advertisement entry in Address Family for a peer.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvCo.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvConditionMap
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvCo.description: The condition-map to apply for this conditional advertisement entry.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvIs.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvIsExistMap
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvIs.description: Set this value to true(1) if the condition-map specified should be applied as an exist-map. If the condition-map should be applied as a non-exist-map, set it to false(2).

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvSe.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvSequenceNum
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvSe.description: The sequence number of this conditional advertisement entry.

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvSt.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvStatus
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvSt.description: This value will be advertise(1) if the status of this advertise-map is evaluated as advertise based on the condition-map. Otherwise it is withdraw(2).

juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvRo.name: juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvRowStatus
juniBgpPeerAddressFamilyConditionalAdvRo.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo, destroy

juniBgpPeerGroupTable.name: juniBgpPeerGroupTable
juniBgpPeerGroupTable.description: The Juniper BGP Peer Group Table describes the BGP-specific characteristics of peer groups.

juniBgpPeerGroupEntry.name: juniBgpPeerGroupEntry
juniBgpPeerGroupEntry.description: The BGP Peer Group Entry describes BGP-specific characteristics of one peer group.

juniBgpPeerGroupVrfName.name: juniBgpPeerGroupVrfName
juniBgpPeerGroupVrfName.description: The name of the VPN Routing Forwarding (VRF) instance in which this peer-group is configured. The empty string indicates that this peer-group is not in a VRF.

juniBgpPeerGroupGroupName.name: juniBgpPeerGroupGroupName
juniBgpPeerGroupGroupName.description: The name of the Peer group this instance configures.

juniBgpPeerGroupAdminStatus.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAdminStatus
juniBgpPeerGroupAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the BGP connection. A transition from 'stop' to 'start' will cause the BGP Start Event to be generated. A transition from 'start' to 'stop' will cause the BGP Stop Event to be generated. This parameter can be used to restart BGP peer connections. Care should be used in providing write access to this object without adequate authentication.

juniBgpPeerGroupRemoteAsNumber.name: juniBgpPeerGroupRemoteAsNumber
juniBgpPeerGroupRemoteAsNumber.description: Deprecated. The peer's autonomous system number. This object has been replaced by juniBgpPeerGroupFourOctetRemoteAsNumber. It is still possible to get and set this object, but if the actual remote AS number is greater than 65535, getting this object returns 23456 (AS-TRANS).

juniBgpPeerGroupRetryInterval.name: juniBgpPeerGroupRetryInterval
juniBgpPeerGroupRetryInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the ConnectRetry timer. The suggested value for this timer is 120 seconds.

juniBgpPeerGroupConfigHoldTime.name: juniBgpPeerGroupConfigHoldTime
juniBgpPeerGroupConfigHoldTime.description: Time interval in seconds for the Hold Time configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. This value is placed in an OPEN message sent to this peer by this BGP speaker, and is compared with the Hold Time field in an OPEN message received from the peer when determining the Hold Time (bgpPeerHoldTime) with the peer. This value must not be less than three seconds if it is not zero (0) in which case the Hold Time is NOT to be established with the peer. The suggested value for this timer is 90 seconds.

juniBgpPeerGroupConfigKeepAliveInterval.name: juniBgpPeerGroupConfigKeepAliveInterval
juniBgpPeerGroupConfigKeepAliveInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. The value of this object will only determine the KEEPALIVE messages' frequency relative to the value specified in bgpPeerHoldTimeConfigured; the actual time interval for the KEEPALIVE messages is indicated by bgpPeerKeepAlive. A reasonable maximum value for this timer would be configured to be one third of that of bgpPeerHoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), no periodical KEEPALIVE messages are sent to the peer after the BGP connection has been established. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

juniBgpPeerGroupAsOriginationInterval.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAsOriginationInterval
juniBgpPeerGroupAsOriginationInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinASOriginationInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 10 seconds.

juniBgpPeerGroupAdvertisementInterval.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAdvertisementInterval
juniBgpPeerGroupAdvertisementInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinRouteAdvertisementInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

juniBgpPeerGroupWeight.name: juniBgpPeerGroupWeight
juniBgpPeerGroupWeight.description: The weight assigned to routes learned from peer.

juniBgpPeerGroupEbgpMultihopTtl.name: juniBgpPeerGroupEbgpMultihopTtl
juniBgpPeerGroupEbgpMultihopTtl.description: Maximum number of hops to the external peer (only relevant if EBGP multihop turned on).

juniBgpPeerGroupUpdateSource.name: juniBgpPeerGroupUpdateSource
juniBgpPeerGroupUpdateSource.description: The source IP address for peer connections.

juniBgpPeerGroupMd5Password.name: juniBgpPeerGroupMd5Password
juniBgpPeerGroupMd5Password.description: The password for MD5 authentication. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero.

juniBgpPeerGroupMaxUpdateSize.name: juniBgpPeerGroupMaxUpdateSize
juniBgpPeerGroupMaxUpdateSize.description: The maximum size in bytes of transmitted UPDATE messages.

juniBgpPeerGroupResetConnectionType.name: juniBgpPeerGroupResetConnectionType
juniBgpPeerGroupResetConnectionType.description: Writing a value to this object causes the sessions to all peers in the peer-group to be cleared; the value determines what type of clear is executed (hard clear, soft clear in, soft clear out, etc.). Reading this object has no effect and always returns resetTypeNoop.

juniBgpPeerGroupRowStatus.name: juniBgpPeerGroupRowStatus
juniBgpPeerGroupRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy

juniBgpPeerGroupLocalAsNumber.name: juniBgpPeerGroupLocalAsNumber
juniBgpPeerGroupLocalAsNumber.description: Deprecated. The local autonomous system number to be used for members. of this peer-group. Value zero (0) means that the global local automous system number (as specified in the object juniBgpPeerGroupLocalAsNumber) is used. This object has been replaced by juniBgpPeerGroupFourOctetLocalAsNumber. It is still possible to get and set this object, but if the actual local AS number is greater than 65535, getting this object returns AS-TRANS (23456).

juniBgpPeerGroupFourOctetRemoteAsNumber.name: juniBgpPeerGroupFourOctetRemoteAsNumber
juniBgpPeerGroupFourOctetRemoteAsNumber.description: The peer's four-octet autonomous system number.

juniBgpPeerGroupFourOctetLocalAsNumber.name: juniBgpPeerGroupFourOctetLocalAsNumber
juniBgpPeerGroupFourOctetLocalAsNumber.description: The four-octet local autonomous system number to be used for this peer. Value zero (0) means that the global local automous system number (as specified in the object juniBgpPeerGroupFourOctetLocalAsNumber) is used.

juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.name: juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilitiesOption
juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.description: Set this object to true if the capabilities option should be included in OPEN messages sent to this peer. Even if this object is set to true, BGP may decide not to include the capabilities option in OPEN messages sent to this peer (for example when it is detected that the peer does not support capability negotiation). The juniBgpPeerSentCapabilitiesOption can be used to determine whether or not the OPEN message sent to the peer actually contained the capabilities option.

juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.name: juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilityRouteRefresh
juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.description: Set this object to true if the route-refresh capability should be advertised to this peer. Even if this object is set to true, BGP may decide not to advertise the route-refresh capability to this peer (for example when it is detected that the peer does not support capability negotiation or when it is detected that the peer does not support the route-refresh capability and incorrectly sends an unsupported capability notification). The juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityRouteRefresh can be used to determine whether or not the capability was actually advertised to the peer.

juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.name: juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilityRouteRefreshCisco
juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.description: Set this object to true if the route-refresh-cisco capability should be advertised to this peer. Even if this object is set to true, BGP may decide not to advertise the route-refresh-cisco capability to this peer (for example when it is detected that the peer does not support capability negotiation or when it is detected that the peer does not support the route-refresh-cisco capability and incorrectly sends an unsupported capability notification). The juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityRouteRefreshCisco can be used to determine whether or not the capability was actually advertised to the peer.

juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.name: juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilityFourOctetAsNumbers
juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.description: Set this object to true if the four-octet-as-numbers capability should be advertised to this peer. Even if this object is set to true, BGP may decide not to advertise the four-octet-as-numbers capability to this peer (for example when it is detected that the peer does not support capability negotiation or when it is detected that the peer does not support the four-octet-as-numbers capability and incorrectly sends an unsupported capability notification). The juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityFourOctetAsNumbers can be used to determine whether or not the capability was actually advertised to the peer.

juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.name: juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilityDynamicCapabilityNeg
juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.description: Set this object to true if the dynamic-capability-negotiation capability should be advertised to this peer. Even if this object is set to true, BGP may decide not to advertise the dynamic-capability-negotiation capability to this peer (for example when it is detected that the peer does not support capability negotiation or when it is detected that the peer does not support the dynamic-capability-negotiation capability and incorrectly sends an unsupported capability notification). The juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityDynamicCapabilityNeg can be used to determine whether or not the capability was actually advertised to the peer.

juniBgpPeerGroupUnconfiguredAttributes.name: juniBgpPeerGroupUnconfiguredAttributes
juniBgpPeerGroupUnconfiguredAttributes.description: On get each bit indicates whether the corresponding attribute is configured or unconfigured: 0 = The attribute is configured (i.e. the configured value is the operational value). 1 = The attribute is unconfigured (i.e. the operational value is inherited from the a higher level which could be the default value). Getting the attribute value itself always returns the operational value of that attribute regardless of whether the attribute is configured or unconfigured.
