On write each bit indicates whether or not the corresponding attribute should be set to the unconfigured state: 0 = No operation (i.e. do not change the state of the attribute). 1 = Set the attribute to the unconfigured state. Setting an attribute to a value has the automatic side-effect of setting the bit with the same name to zero.

juniBgpPeerGroupSiteOfOrigin.name: juniBgpPeerGroupSiteOfOrigin
juniBgpPeerGroupSiteOfOrigin.description: The site-of-origin. This site-of-origin is added to the extended communities for all routes received from the peer. When sending routes to this peer-group all routes with this extended community are filtered. The null extended community (all 8 bytes zero) means that no site-of-origin is configured for this peer. It is not allowed to set this object to any extended community other than a site-of-origin type of extended community or null.

juniBgpPeerGroupLenient.name: juniBgpPeerGroupLenient
juniBgpPeerGroupLenient.description: Enable Lenient behavior for member peers so that they are more tolerant of finite state machine errors and malformed messages received from the remote peer and avoid terminating the peer session whenever possible.

juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.name: juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilityOldDynamicCapabilityNeg
juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.description: Set this object to true if the deprecated-dynamic-capability- negotiation capability should be advertised to this peer. Even if this object is set to true, BGP may decide not to advertise the deprecated-dynamic-capability-negotiation capability to this peer (for example when it is detected that the peer does not support capability negotiation or when it is detected that the peer does not support the deprecated-dynamic-capability-negotiation capability and incorrectly sends an unsupported capability notification). The juniBgpPeerSentCapabilityOldDynamicCapabilityNeg can be used to determine whether or not the capability was actually advertised to the peer.

juniBgpPeerGroupPassive.name: juniBgpPeerGroupPassive
juniBgpPeerGroupPassive.description: Set this object to true(1) to make members of this peer-group passive.

juniBgpPeerGroupConfiguredPeerType.name: juniBgpPeerGroupConfiguredPeerType
juniBgpPeerGroupConfiguredPeerType.description: The type of the members of the peer-group.

juniBgpPeerGroupAllowAccessListName.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAllowAccessListName
juniBgpPeerGroupAllowAccessListName.description: The name of the access-list for promiscuous peers. When an incoming connection arrives whose remote address matches this access-list the connection is accepted and a dynamic peer is created. An empty string means that promiscuous peers are disabled for this peer-group.

juniBgpPeerGroupAllowMaxPeers.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAllowMaxPeers
juniBgpPeerGroupAllowMaxPeers.description: The maximum number of dynamic peers for this peer-group. Zero means that there is no limit.

juniBgpPeerGroupCurrentDynamicPeerCount.name: juniBgpPeerGroupCurrentDynamicPeerCount
juniBgpPeerGroupCurrentDynamicPeerCount.description: The current number of dynamic peers for this peer-group.

juniBgpPeerGroupHighWaterMarkDynamicPeer.name: juniBgpPeerGroupHighWaterMarkDynamicPeerCount
juniBgpPeerGroupHighWaterMarkDynamicPeer.description: The high water mark for the number of dynamic peers for this peer-group.

juniBgpPeerGroupRejectedDynamicPeerCount.name: juniBgpPeerGroupRejectedDynamicPeerCount
juniBgpPeerGroupRejectedDynamicPeerCount.description: The number of connection attempts for dynamic peers that were rejected because the number number of dynamic peers was reached.

juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.name: juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilityGracefulRestart
juniBgpPeerGroupShouldAdvertiseCapabilit.description: Set this object to true if the graceful-restart capability should be advertised to all members of the peer-group.

juniBgpPeerGroupGracefulRestartRestartTi.name: juniBgpPeerGroupGracefulRestartRestartTime
juniBgpPeerGroupGracefulRestartRestartTi.description: The restart-time advertised in the graceful-restart capability sent to members of this peer-group. This is the estimated time (in seconds) it will take for the BGP session to be re-established after a restart. This can be used to speed up routing convergence by the peer in case that this BGP speaker does not come back after a restart. This value (if configured) overrides the global value configured in juniBgpGracefulRestartRestartTime.

juniBgpPeerGroupGracefulRestartStalePath.name: juniBgpPeerGroupGracefulRestartStalePathsTime
juniBgpPeerGroupGracefulRestartStalePath.description: The maximum amount of time in seconds we keep stale routes after the session to a member of this peer-group goes down. This value (if configured) overrides the global value configured in juniBgpGracefulRestartStalePathsTime.

juniBgpPeerGroupBfdEnabled.name: juniBgpPeerGroupBfdEnabled
juniBgpPeerGroupBfdEnabled.description: Value true(1) the BFD is enabled for this peer-group.

juniBgpPeerGroupBfdMinTransmitInterval.name: juniBgpPeerGroupBfdMinTransmitInterval
juniBgpPeerGroupBfdMinTransmitInterval.description: The minimum interval (in milliseconds) between BFD packets sent to the remote BFD speaker. In other words, it specifies the maximum rate at which we are willing to send BFD packets.

juniBgpPeerGroupBfdMinReceiveInterval.name: juniBgpPeerGroupBfdMinReceiveInterval
juniBgpPeerGroupBfdMinReceiveInterval.description: The minimum interval (in milliseconds) between BFD packets received from the remote BFD speaker. In other words, it specifies the maximum rate at which we are willing to receive BFD packets.

juniBgpPeerGroupBfdMultiplier.name: juniBgpPeerGroupBfdMultiplier
juniBgpPeerGroupBfdMultiplier.description: How many BFD packets can be missed before the BFD session is declared down.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyTable.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyTable
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyTable.description: The Juniper BGP Peer Group Address Family Table describes the BGP-specific attributes of an Address Family for a peer group.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyEntry.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyEntry
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyEntry.description: The BGP Peer Group Address Family Entry describes.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyVrfName.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyVrfName
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyVrfName.description: The name of the VPN Routing Forwarding (VRF) instance in which this peer-group is configured. The empty string indicates that this peer-group is not in a VRF.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAfi.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAfi
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAfi.description: The AFI of the address-family in which this peer-group is configured.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilySafi.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilySafi
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilySafi.description: The SAFI of the address-family in which this peer-group is configured.

juniBgpPeerGroupGroupAddressFamilyGroupN.name: juniBgpPeerGroupGroupAddressFamilyGroupName
juniBgpPeerGroupGroupAddressFamilyGroupN.description: The name of the Peer group this instance configures.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyDefaultOrig.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyDefaultOriginate
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyDefaultOrig.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to advertise a default route to this peer, if present.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyNextHopSelf.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyNextHopSelf
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyNextHopSelf.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to always advertise this router as the next hop.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilySendCommuni.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilySendCommunity
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilySendCommuni.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to send COMMUNITIES attributes in updates.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyDistributeL.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyDistributeListIn
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyDistributeL.description: The inbound distribute IP access list name.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyDistributeL.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyDistributeListOut
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyDistributeL.description: The outbound distribute IP access list name.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyPrefixListI.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyPrefixListIn
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyPrefixListI.description: The inbound IP prefix list name.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyPrefixListO.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyPrefixListOut
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyPrefixListO.description: The outbound IP prefix list name.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyPrefixTreeI.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyPrefixTreeIn
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyPrefixTreeI.description: The inbound IP prefix tree name.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyPrefixTreeO.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyPrefixTreeOut
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyPrefixTreeO.description: The outbound IP prefix tree name.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyFilterListI.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyFilterListIn
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyFilterListI.description: The inbound filter AS path list name.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyFilterListO.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyFilterListOut
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyFilterListO.description: The outbound filter AS path list name.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyFilterListW.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyFilterListWeight
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyFilterListW.description: The weight filter AS path list name.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyFilterListW.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyFilterListWeightValue
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyFilterListW.description: The weight to apply on weight filter list matches.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteMapIn.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteMapIn
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteMapIn.description: The inbound route-map name. An empty string means no inbound route-map.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteMapOut.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteMapOut
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteMapOut.description: The outbound route-map name. An empty string means no outbound route-map.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteReflec.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteReflectorClient
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteReflec.description: The peer is a route reflector client.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteLimitW.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteLimitWarn
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteLimitW.description: Log a warning if pathCount exceeds this value.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteLimitR.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteLimitReset
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteLimitR.description: Reset connection is pathCount exceeds this value.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteLimitW.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteLimitWarnOnly
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteLimitW.description: Warn, but do not reset, if the path limit is exceeded.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRemovePriva.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRemovePrivateAs
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRemovePriva.description: Remove private AS numbers from AS paths.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyUnsuppressM.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyUnsuppressMap
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyUnsuppressM.description: The unsuppress route-map name. Routes which are sent to this peer and which match this route-map are not subject to suppression by summary-only aggregates. An empty string means no unsuppress route-map.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyInboundSoft.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyInboundSoftReconfig
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyInboundSoft.description: Inbound soft-reconfiguration is enabled. If inbound soft-reconfiguration is enabled we keep a copy of each received route before inbound policy was applied.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyResetConnec.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyResetConnectionType
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyResetConnec.description: Writing a value to this object causes one individual address family within the sessions to all peers in the peer-group to be cleared; the value determines what type of clear is executed (hard clear, soft clear in, soft clear out, etc.). Note that hard clearing an address family within a session will bounce the session and thus also affect the other address families in the session. Reading this object has no effect and always returns resetTypeNoop.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRowStatus.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRowStatus
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAsOverride.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAsOverride
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAsOverride.description: Replace the AS number of the peer by our own AS number in the AS-path attribute in UPDATEs sent to this peer-group.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAllowAsIn.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAllowAsIn
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAllowAsIn.description: The maximum number of times our own AS number is allowed to occur in a received AS-path before that received route is considered to be a loop and therefore rejected.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilySendExtende.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilySendExtendedCommunity
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilySendExtende.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to send EXTENDED-COMMUNITIES attributes in updates.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAdvertiseCa.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPrefixListOrfSend
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAdvertiseCa.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to send PREFIX-LIST ORF SEND CAPABILITY in Open Message.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAdvertiseCa.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAdvertiseCapPrefixListCiscoOrfSend
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyAdvertiseCa.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to send PREFIX-LIST-CISCO ORF SEND CAPABILITY in Open Message.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyMaximumPref.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyMaximumPrefixStrict
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyMaximumPref.description: If the juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyInboundSoftReconfig object is set to true then routes which were rejected by inbound policy are stored in memory anyway. The juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyMaximumPrefixStrict object determines whether or not these routes count towards the maximum number of routes from the peer-group members (as configured in juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteLimitWarn and/or juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyRouteLimitReset).

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyUnconfigure.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyUnconfiguredAttributes
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyUnconfigure.description: On get each bit indicates whether the corresponding attribute is configured or unconfigured: 0 = The attribute is configured (i.e. the configured value is the operational value). 1 = The attribute is unconfigured (i.e. the operational value is inherited from the a higher level which could be the default value). Getting the attribute value itself always returns the operational value of that attribute regardless of whether the attribute is configured or unconfigured. On write each bit indicates whether or not the corresponding attribute should be set to the unconfigured state: 0 = No operation (i.e. do not change the state of the attribute). 1 = Set the attribute to the unconfigured state. Setting an attribute to a value has the automatic side-effect of setting the bit with the same name to zero.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilySendLabel.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilySendLabel
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilySendLabel.description: Send labeled prefixes to this peer for this address-family.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyDefaultOrig.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyDefaultOriginateRouteMap
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyDefaultOrig.description: The route-map to apply to the default route which is advertised to this peer-group as a result of setting juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyDefaultOriginate to true. An empty string means that no route-map is applied.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyNextHopUnch.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyNextHopUnchanged
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyNextHopUnch.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to always advertise the next-hop unchanged to this peer-group in this address-family.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditional.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditionalAdvTable
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditional.description: The Juniper BGP Peer Group Address Family Conditional Advertisement Table describes the BGP conditional advertisement attributes in an Address Family for a peer-group.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditional.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditionalAdvEntry
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditional.description: The Juniper BGP Peer Group Address Family Conditional Advertisement Entry describes a specific conditional advertisement entry in an Address Family for a peer-group.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditional.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditionalAdvConditionMap
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditional.description: The condition-map to apply for this conditional advertisement entry.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditional.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditionalAdvIsExistMap
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditional.description: Set this value to true(1) if the condition-map specified should be applied as an exist-map. If the condition-map should be applied as a non-exist-map, set it to false(2).

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditional.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditionalAdvSequenceNum
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditional.description: The sequence number of this conditional advertisement entry.

juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditional.name: juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditionalAdvStatus
juniBgpPeerGroupAddressFamilyConditional.description: This value will be advertise(1) if the status of this advertise-map is evaluated as advertise based on the condition-map. Otherwise it is withdraw(2).

juniBgpNetworkTable.description: The BGP Network Table controls what networks are originated by this BGP router.

juniBgpNetworkVrfName.name: juniBgpNetworkVrfName
juniBgpNetworkVrfName.description: The name of the VPN Routing Forwarding (VRF) instance in which this network is configured. The empty string indicates that this network is not in a VRF.

juniBgpNetworkAfi.name: juniBgpNetworkAfi
juniBgpNetworkAfi.description: The AFI of the address-family in which this network is configured.

juniBgpNetworkSafi.name: juniBgpNetworkSafi
juniBgpNetworkSafi.description: The SAFI of the address-family in which this network is configured.

juniBgpNetworkIpAddrPrefix.name: juniBgpNetworkIpAddrPrefix
juniBgpNetworkIpAddrPrefix.description: An IP address prefix in the Network Layer Reachability Information field. This object is an IP address containing the prefix with length specified by bgpRouteIpAddrPrefixLen. Any bits beyond the length specified by bgpRouteIpAddrPrefixLen are zeroed.

juniBgpNetworkIpAddrPrefixLen.name: juniBgpNetworkIpAddrPrefixLen
juniBgpNetworkIpAddrPrefixLen.description: Length in bits of the IP address prefix in the Network Layer Reachability Information field.

juniBgpNetworkBackdoor.name: juniBgpNetworkBackdoor
juniBgpNetworkBackdoor.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to enable BGP backdoor in this network. This object can only be set at row creation.

juniBgpNetworkRowStatus.name: juniBgpNetworkRowStatus
juniBgpNetworkRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy

juniBgpNetworkWeightSpecified.name: juniBgpNetworkWeightSpecified
juniBgpNetworkWeightSpecified.description: If this object is set to true(1) then the BGP weight of this network is set to the value specified in juniBgpNetworkWeightValue. This object can only be set at row creation.

juniBgpNetworkWeight.name: juniBgpNetworkWeight
juniBgpNetworkWeight.description: If juniBgpNetworkWeight specified is set to true(1) then this object specifies the weight of the network. Otherwise the weight of the network is determined by the IGP metric of the prefix. This object can only be set at row creation.

juniBgpNetworkRouteMap.name: juniBgpNetworkRouteMap
juniBgpNetworkRouteMap.description: The name of the route-map used to set the path attributes of this network. A zero length route-map name means don't use a route-map for this. This object can only be set at row creation.

juniBgpNetworkUnconfiguredAttributes.name: juniBgpNetworkUnconfiguredAttributes

juniBgpAggregateEntry.description: An instance in the list of route aggregation.

juniBgpAggregateVrfName.name: juniBgpAggregateVrfName
juniBgpAggregateVrfName.description: The name of the VPN Routing Forwarding (VRF) instance in which this aggregate is configured. The empty string indicates that this aggregate is not in a VRF.

juniBgpAggregateAfi.name: juniBgpAggregateAfi
juniBgpAggregateAfi.description: The AFI of the address-family in which this aggregate is configured.

juniBgpAggregateSafi.name: juniBgpAggregateSafi
juniBgpAggregateSafi.description: The SAFI of the address-family in which this aggregate is configured.

juniBgpAggregateIpAddrPrefix.name: juniBgpAggregateIpAddrPrefix
juniBgpAggregateIpAddrPrefix.description: An IP address prefix in the Network Layer Reachability Information field. This object is an IP address containing the prefix with length specified by bgpRouteIpAddrPrefixLen. Any bits beyond the length specified by bgpRouteIpAddrPrefixLen are zeroed.

juniBgpAggregateIpAddrPrefixLen.name: juniBgpAggregateIpAddrPrefixLen
juniBgpAggregateIpAddrPrefixLen.description: Length in bits of the IP address prefix in the Network Layer Reachability Information field.

juniBgpAggregateAsSet.name: juniBgpAggregateAsSet
juniBgpAggregateAsSet.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to generate AS_set path information by creating an aggregate entry that consists of all elements contained in all paths that are being summarized. This object can only be set at row creation.

juniBgpAggregateSummaryOnly.name: juniBgpAggregateSummaryOnly
juniBgpAggregateSummaryOnly.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to filter specific routes from updates. By doing that, advertisements of more specific routes will be suppressed to all neighbors. This object can only be set at row creation.

juniBgpAggregateAttributeMap.name: juniBgpAggregateAttributeMap
juniBgpAggregateAttributeMap.description: The name of the route-map used to set the attributes of the aggregate An empty string means no route-map for this purpose.

juniBgpAggregateAdvertiseMap.name: juniBgpAggregateAdvertiseMap
juniBgpAggregateAdvertiseMap.description: The name of the route-map used to select routes covered by the aggregate (for as-set aggregates the path attributes of the aggregate route are created by summarizing the path attributes of the covered routes). An empty string means no route-map for this purpose.

juniBgpAggregateSuppressMap.description: The suppress route-map name. If a suppress route-map has been specified, all routes which are covered by the aggregate and which match the suppress route-map are suppressed. An empty string means no inbound route-map.

juniBgpVrfEntry.description: The BGP VRF Entry describes BGP-specific characteristics of one VRF.

juniBgpVrfName.name: juniBgpVrfName
juniBgpVrfName.description: The name of the VPN Routing Forwarding (VRF) instance.

juniBgpVrfSynchronization.name: juniBgpVrfSynchronization
juniBgpVrfSynchronization.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to have IGP route synchronization enabled.

juniBgpVrfAutoSummary.name: juniBgpVrfAutoSummary
juniBgpVrfAutoSummary.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to automatically summarize redistributed routes to their natural network mask.

juniBgpVrfExternalDistance.name: juniBgpVrfExternalDistance
juniBgpVrfExternalDistance.description: Obsolete administrative distance for external routes. Replaced by juniBgpAddressFamilyExternalDistance.

juniBgpVrfInternalDistance.name: juniBgpVrfInternalDistance
juniBgpVrfInternalDistance.description: Obsolete administrative distance for internal routes. Replaced by juniBgpAddressFamilyInternalDistance.

juniBgpVrfLocalDistance.name: juniBgpVrfLocalDistance
juniBgpVrfLocalDistance.description: Obsolete administrative distance for local routes. Replaced by juniBgpAddressFamilyLocalDistance.

juniBgpVrfResetConnectionType.name: juniBgpVrfResetConnectionType
juniBgpVrfResetConnectionType.description: Writing a value to this object causes the sessions to all peers in this VRF to be cleared; the value determines what type of clear is executed (hard clear, soft clear in, soft clear out, etc.). juniBgpVrfAddUnicastRoutesToMulticastVie.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to add routes learnt by IPv4 Unicast BGP to the multicast route table.

juniBgpVrfMaximumPathsEbgp.name: juniBgpVrfMaximumPathsEbgp
juniBgpVrfMaximumPathsEbgp.description: The maximum number of routes received from EBGP peers which BGP can select as equal cost. Zero means that routes from EBGP peers cannot be selected as equal cost.

juniBgpVrfMaximumPathsIbgp.name: juniBgpVrfMaximumPathsIbgp
juniBgpVrfMaximumPathsIbgp.description: The maximum number of routes received from IBGP peers which BGP can select as equal cost. Zero means that routes from IBGP peers cannot be selected as equal cost.

juniBgpVrfMaximumPathsEIbgp.description: The maximum number of routes received from both EBGP and IBGP peers which BGP can select as equal cost. Zero means that routes from both EBGP and IBGP peers cannot be selected as equal cost.

juniBgpVrfCarriersCarrierModeEnabled.name: juniBgpVrfCarriersCarrierModeEnabled
juniBgpVrfCarriersCarrierModeEnabled.description: Obsolete the BGP carrier's carrier flag since there is no need for it when in carrier's carrier mode.

juniBgpAddressFamilyTable.name: juniBgpAddressFamilyTable
juniBgpAddressFamilyTable.description: The BGP AddressFamily Entry describes BGP-specific characteristics of one AddressFamily.

juniBgpAddressFamilyVrfName.name: juniBgpAddressFamilyVrfName
juniBgpAddressFamilyVrfName.description: The name of the VPN Routing Forwarding (VRF) instance in which this address-family is configured. The empty string indicates that this address-family is not in a VRF.

juniBgpAddressFamilyDefaultOriginate.name: juniBgpAddressFamilyDefaultOriginate
juniBgpAddressFamilyDefaultOriginate.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to advertise a default route, if present.

juniBgpAddressFamilyRouteFlapDampening.name: juniBgpAddressFamilyRouteFlapDampening
juniBgpAddressFamilyRouteFlapDampening.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to enable route flap dampening.

juniBgpAddressFamilyDampeningMaxHoldDown.name: juniBgpAddressFamilyDampeningMaxHoldDownTime
juniBgpAddressFamilyDampeningMaxHoldDown.description: Maximum route holddown time, in seconds.

juniBgpAddressFamilyDampeningHalfLifeRea.name: juniBgpAddressFamilyDampeningHalfLifeReachable
juniBgpAddressFamilyDampeningHalfLifeRea.description: Figure of merit half life for reachable routes, in seconds.

juniBgpAddressFamilyDampeningHalfLifeUnr.name: juniBgpAddressFamilyDampeningHalfLifeUnreachable
juniBgpAddressFamilyDampeningHalfLifeUnr.description: Figure of merit half life for unreachable routes, in seconds.

juniBgpAddressFamilyDampeningRouteMapNam.description: The name of the route-map used to determine which routes are dampened and which aren't and to set the dampening parameters for those routes which are dampenend. A zero length route-map name means don't use a route-map for this.

juniBgpAddressFamilyLocalDistance.description: The administrative distance for local routes.

juniBgpAddressFamilyDefaultOriginateRout.name: juniBgpAddressFamilyDefaultOriginateRouteMap
juniBgpAddressFamilyDefaultOriginateRout.description: The route-map to apply to the default route which is advertised as a result of setting juniBgpAddressFamilyDefaultOriginate to true. An empty string means that no route-map is applied.

juniBgpAddressFamilyIpIntfProfileNameFor.name: juniBgpAddressFamilyIpIntfProfileNameForMplsHeads
juniBgpAddressFamilyIpIntfProfileNameFor.description: Obsolete the name of the IP interface profile used by BGP to create IP dynamic interfaces on top of MPLS stacked tunnel heads. When support for BGP-created IP dynamic interfaces was removed, BGP profile names were obsoleted too.

juniBgpAddressFamilyIpIntfProfileNameFor.name: juniBgpAddressFamilyIpIntfProfileNameForMplsTails

juniBgpAddressFamilyCheckVpnNextHops.name: juniBgpAddressFamilyCheckVpnNextHops
juniBgpAddressFamilyCheckVpnNextHops.description: If this object is set to true, the reachability of the next-hops of routes in this address-family are checked. juniBgpAddressFamilyPathSelectionIsDefer.name: juniBgpAddressFamilyPathSelectionIsDeferred
juniBgpAddressFamilyPathSelectionIsDefer.description: Is path selection for the address-family currently deferred?

juniBgpStorageMaxPeerPoolSize.name: juniBgpStorageMaxPeerPoolSize
juniBgpStorageMaxPeerPoolSize.description: Obsolete maximum size of the peer pool in entries.

juniBgpStorageInitialPeerAfPoolSize.description: Obsolete initial size of the peer-address-family pool in entries. juniBgpStorageMaxPeerAfPoolSize.name: juniBgpStorageMaxPeerAfPoolSize
juniBgpStorageMaxPeerAfPoolSize.description: Obsolete maximum size of the peer-address-family pool in entries.

juniBgpStorageInitialPeerGroupPoolSize.name: juniBgpStorageInitialPeerGroupPoolSize
juniBgpStorageInitialPeerGroupPoolSize.description: Obsolete initial size of the peer-group pool in entries. One entry is allocated from the peer-group pool for each peer-group configured in BGP.
